args: Okay! What should we do next?
I can't believe you still have so much\nenergy after everything we've... Huh?
What is it, {player_name}?\n...Oh, are these raindrops?
I got a feelin' those clouds mean business.
Whoa! It's really coming down! Let's take\nshelter in that cave until it clears up.
Well, of course you are.\nWe've been frolicking in the sea.
Ha ha, I guess you've got a point.\n...Huh. Where did everyone else go?
Looks like we were separated in our rush\nto escape the rain.
But I wouldn't worry—I'm sure they're\nall dry and warm somewhere nearby.
You're probably right. I suppose we'll just\nwait it out here until the rain lets up.
Er, but aren't you going to get\neven wetter if you stay there?
Maybe, but only a little.\nDon't worry about it.
Oh, don't be absurd. Come closer\nbefore you catch your death.
You're clearly trying to stand somewhere\nthat will shield me from the rain.
Because I know you're the kind of person\nwho is always putting others' needs first.\nIt's something I respect greatly about you.
Not at all. In fact, I've learned a\ntremendous amount from you.
As a preacher, I'm usually the one\nteaching others—but with you,\nit's the other way around.
I've learned a lot from you as well.
Sure. For example, you're always focused\non what you want to achieve, and you're\nnot afraid to own up to your mistakes.
That's been an important lesson for me,\nand also something of an inspiration.
It's also why I know you'll always\nend up finding the right answer.
Oh, I don't know about that...
You just did it earlier when you were\nworrying about your behavior with\nthose two thugs on the beach.
For what it's worth, I think your\nfinal conclusion was a good one.
I'm happy that you think so highly of me,\nbut I think you're wrong in this case.
The reason I told those two off earlier\nwasn't because I was concerned about\ngood behavior. It was...um...
It was because I didn't want anyone\ngetting in the way of my fun with... Um...
It was because I didn't want anyone\ngetting in the way of my fun with you!\n...There. I said it.
I wasn't really worried about other\npeople's happiness in that moment—\nI was only thinking about my own.
Does that lower your opinion of me\ndown a peg or three?
Not at all. In fact, I feel the same.
I don't want anyone interrupting the fun\nI'm having with you, Elisanne, Ranzal,\nor anyone else!
It's also the same reason I fight—\nso I can bring happiness to people\nall across the world.
Never mind. I knew from the start the\nkind of person you are, so I have no\none to blame here but myself.
I'm just a fool for getting my hopes up.
But let me give you a warning.
I think it's wonderful that you have\nsuch a grand goal in mind for the\nentire world. I really do.
But you must also pay attention to things\nthat are happening right in front of you.
Well, I'm certainly not going to\nexplain it to you further!
...We should go look for the others.
It stopped raining ages ago, you fool man!
